title: Police Plea After 85-Year-Old Sydney Grandfather Kidnapped In Alleged Mistaken Identity | 10 News
description: Police have made a desperate plea for the safe return of a grandfather kidnapped from his northwest Sydney home four days ago.  Disturbing video is circulating through the underworld, as it's confirmed the 85-year-old has been taken in a case of mistaken identity.  Olivia Blunden has the details. title: India Celebrates After Win Over Pakistan In T20 World Cup | 10 News
description: Celebrations have erupted across India after the team’s T20 World Cup victory over Pakistan on Sunday.  Fans poured onto the streets for high-energy festivities in Mumbai and Sri Lanka, cheering the win with drums, chanting, fireworks and proudly waving the nation’s flag to mark a historic win for the Indian cricket team.  India defeated Pakistan by 61 runs at R. Premadasa Stadium, Colombo, Sri Lanka. title: Ute Plunges Off Collapsed Bridge In New Zealand's North Island | 10 News
description: Eyewitness video has captured a Ute partially submerged in floodwater after a highway bridge collapsed amid heavy rains battering New Zealand’s North Island.  Parts of Waikato were hit by heavy rain, severe flooding and slips overnight, prompting evacuations across the region.  It’s understood the driver of the Ute was uninjured, however, another man was found dead after his vehicle was submerged in floodwaters between Pirongia and Ōtorohanga on Friday night.  Tens of thousands are without power across the lower North Island and several States of Emergency remain in place. title: How TikTok Exposed Coles And Helped Spark One Of Australia’s Biggest Consumer Court Cases | 10 News+
description: Content creator Paniora Nukunuku is known for calling out supermarket price gouging online, but he never thought his TikTok videos would help trigger one of the biggest consumer court battles in Australian history.   It was social media posts that helped tip off Australia's consumer watchdog, the ACCC, which today began landmark legal action against Coles in the Federal Court. title: DNA Recovered From Glove Found Near Nancy Guthrie’s Home | 10 News+
description: Investigators have recovered DNA from a glove found near the home of ‘Today’ host Savannah Guthrie’s mother.   The glove appears to match those worn by a masked person caught on doorbell camera outside Nancy Guthrie’s front door in Tucson the night she disappeared.   10 News+ spoke to forensic criminologist Dr Laura Pettler about the ongoing investigation into the alleged abduction.
